---
description: Best practices for Angular development focusing on performance and maintainability
globs: ["**/*.ts", "**/*.component.ts", "**/*.service.ts", "**/*.module.ts"]
alwaysApply: true
---
- Use Angular CLI for project setup and management
- Implement OnPush change detection strategy for better performance
- Use Observables for asynchronous operations
- Keep components small and focused on a single responsibility
- Utilize Angular's dependency injection system
- Follow Angular's style guide for naming conventions
- Implement lazy loading for feature modules
- Use standalone components when appropriate
- Implement proper error handling and loading states
- Document component inputs, outputs, and public methods
